        "intro": "If your parent needs daily help with activities like bathing, dressing, or managing medications — and is at risk of nursing home placement — Alabama's Elderly and Disabled Medicaid Waiver can pay for home care services to keep them living independently.\n\nThe waiver covers personal care, homemaker services, companion care, respite care, adult day programs, and meal delivery with no yearly service limits. Because services are tailored through a person-centered care plan, your parent gets exactly the support they need rather than a one-size-fits-all package.\n\nTo qualify, your parent must meet Medicaid's financial requirements (income up to $2,829/month, assets under $2,000) and pass a clinical assessment showing they need nursing facility level care. There is a waiting list for those not already on Medicaid.",
