            "question": "My disabled adult son is 35 — can he qualify for this waiver?",
            "answer": "Yes. Despite the name 'Elderly and Disabled,' there's no minimum age requirement. Disabled adults of any age can qualify, including children. For applicants under 18, only the child's income and assets count, not the parents'."
