        "intro": "If your parent is 55+ and needs nursing home-level care but wants to stay at home, PACE could cover all their medical expenses through one coordinated program. Because PACE combines Medicare and Medicaid funding, your parent gets comprehensive care — doctor visits, transportation to appointments, home care services, adult day care, prescription drugs, and even hospital stays — all managed by one medical team with no copays or deductibles.\n\nPACE is only available in specific Arkansas counties, not statewide. The average PACE participant is 76 years old with multiple complex medical conditions. Your parent must be certified by Arkansas DHS as needing nursing facility level of care (daily help with bathing, dressing, or medication management) but able to live safely at home with PACE support.",
