        "intro": "If your parent lives in a nursing home, assisted living facility, or other long-term care facility in Arkansas, they have a right to a free advocate who can investigate complaints and fight for better care. The Arkansas Long-Term Care Ombudsman Program provides trained advocates who work specifically to protect residents' rights and resolve problems within facilities.\n\nOmbudsmen help with issues like poor food quality, unsafe conditions, financial problems, Medicaid eligibility disputes, inappropriate restraints, room temperature problems, and discharge disputes. Because ombudsmen are independent from the facilities, they can investigate complaints without fear of retaliation against your parent.\n\nThis service is completely free and available to any resident in any long-term care facility in Arkansas. You, your parent, or anyone else can contact an ombudsman — no paperwork or eligibility requirements needed.",
