        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "Can Mom keep her house if she qualifies?",
            "answer": "Yes. Your primary home doesn't count toward the $130,000 asset limit, regardless of its value. She can also keep one car and personal belongings."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if her income is just over the limit?",
            "answer": "Income limits update annually, usually in April. If she's close, wait for the new limits or see if any income can be excluded (some deductions may apply). Also check if she qualifies for a lower tier — QI goes up to $1,762/month."
          },
          {
            "question": "Does this affect her other benefits?",
            "answer": "No, Medicare Savings Programs don't reduce Social Security, Medicare, or other benefits. They work alongside existing coverage to reduce medical costs."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if she has a Medicare Advantage plan?",
            "answer": "QMB covers Medicare Advantage cost-sharing too, including copays and deductibles. SLMB and QI only cover the Part B premium portion."
          },
          {
            "question": "How long does approval last?",
            "answer": "Approval requires annual redetermination. Your parent must report income changes within 10 days and complete yearly paperwork to maintain benefits."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if she needs help with the application?",
            "answer": "Contact your county social services office directly — they can help complete the application over the phone or in person. Each county has staff trained on these programs."
          }
        ],
