        "intro": "If your parent is 60+ and needs legal help with housing problems, benefit denials, or elder abuse, they can get free assistance through California's Area Agencies on Aging. These services are available regardless of income — your parent doesn't need to be low-income to qualify, though some areas prioritize those with greater financial need.\n\nThe program covers the legal issues seniors face most: eviction defense, Medicare/Medi-Cal appeals, consumer fraud, simple wills, powers of attorney, and nursing home rights. Each county contracts with different legal aid organizations, so the specific services and contact methods vary by location. Some areas offer ongoing representation, while others provide advice through monthly legal clinics.",
