        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "Can my parent keep their house and still qualify?",
            "answer": "Yes. The primary home doesn't count toward asset limits, regardless of value. One vehicle is also exempt."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if my parent's income is just over the limit?",
            "answer": "Income limits change annually and vary by tier. Contact your county office for current exact amounts — you might qualify for a higher tier (QI instead of SLMB) or limits may have increased."
          },
          {
            "question": "Does this replace my parent's Medicare supplement plan?",
            "answer": "For QMB, yes — it covers all Medicare gaps. For SLMB and QI, your parent may still want a supplement plan since these only cover premiums, not deductibles or copays."
          },
          {
            "question": "My parent already has Medicaid. Do they need this too?",
            "answer": "If they have full Medicaid, they likely don't need this. But if they only have limited Medicaid or are losing coverage, Medicare Savings Programs can fill the gap."
          },
          {
            "question": "How long does approval take?",
            "answer": "Processing time varies by county. Contact your local county Human Services office for current wait times. QI may have additional delays due to funding caps."
          },
          {
            "question": "What happens if my parent's income changes after approval?",
            "answer": "Report income changes to your county office. Depending on the change, they may move between tiers or lose eligibility. Small increases might move them from QMB to SLMB rather than losing all help."
          }
        ],
        "phone": null,
