        "intro": "If your parent struggles with high energy bills, the Weatherization Assistance Program provides free home improvements that reduce heating and cooling costs. The program installs insulation, seals air leaks, and makes safety repairs at no cost to qualifying households.\n\nYour parent automatically qualifies if they receive LEAP, SNAP, TANF, SSI, or AND (requires current approval letter). Otherwise, income limits vary by household size and location — generally 60% of state median income for households of 1-7 people, or 80% of area median income if served by Xcel Energy or other major utilities.\n\nBecause funding is limited, meeting income requirements doesn't guarantee services. Eligible households often join waiting lists, and homes can't be weatherized again for 15 years after previous work.",
