        "intro": "If your parent is 60+ and struggles to shop for groceries or prepare meals safely, they can get hot, nutritious meals delivered to their door Monday through Friday. Each meal provides at least one-third of daily nutrients and includes an entree, vegetables, fruits, bread, and milk. Some areas also provide frozen weekend meals.\n\nMeals on Wheels operates through independent local providers across Colorado, not as one unified program. Because each provider sets their own fees and requirements, what your parent qualifies for depends on exactly where they live. Most areas request donations of $2-$7.50 per meal, but no one is denied service for inability to pay.\n\nYour parent must be assessed as homebound or unable to shop and prepare meals safely. Some areas serve people under 60 with disability documentation or a medical referral.",
