        "intro": "If your parent is 60+ and at risk of nursing home placement, Florida's Home Care for the Elderly program provides in-home services to help them stay in their own home — but only if they have an adult caregiver (age 18+) living with them full-time. This isn't standard home health care. The program requires a dedicated live-in family member or caregiver who can provide daily support for your parent's social, physical, and emotional needs.\n\nServices include personal care assistance, homemaker services, and caregiver support to prevent institutionalization. Your parent must pass a clinical assessment (called a 701B assessment) showing they're at risk of nursing home placement, and their income must be under $2,982/month for a single person (2026 limits).\n\nBecause this program focuses on caregiver-supported aging in place, it's designed for families who can commit to a live-in arrangement — not for parents who live alone or only need occasional help.",
