        "intro": "If your parent is 65+ or disabled and needs nursing home-level care but wants to stay home, Idaho's Aged and Disabled Waiver can pay for home care services instead. The program covers attendant care, homemaker services, adult day health, respite care, home-delivered meals, and medical equipment — services that typically cost $2,000–5,000 per month out of pocket.\n\nTo qualify, your parent must meet strict financial limits (assets under $2,000 for single applicants) and pass a clinical assessment proving they need daily help with activities like bathing, dressing, mobility, eating, or toileting. Because this is a Medicaid waiver program, it also covers all regular medical expenses — doctor visits, prescriptions, hospital care — with no copays or deductibles.",
