        "intro": "If your parent is 55+ and needs significant daily help but wants to avoid a nursing home, PACE provides all their medical care under one coordinated team. Your parent gets primary care, specialists, physical therapy, transportation to appointments, meals, social activities, and home support services — all managed by a single provider instead of juggling multiple doctors and services.\n\nPACE is only available in specific Kansas counties, and your parent must qualify for nursing-home-level care (meaning they need daily help with things like bathing, dressing, or medication management). If your parent has Medicare and Medicaid, or income under about $3,000/month, there's typically no cost. Private pay options exist for those with higher incomes.\n\nBecause PACE covers everything from routine checkups to emergency care, your parent won't need to coordinate between separate providers — one team manages their complete care plan and adjusts services as their needs change.",
