        "intro": "If you're a Kentucky grandparent raising your grandchild because the parents can't, this program connects you with support groups, counseling, and practical help. You'll get assistance accessing services your family needs, plus training on navigating the system.\n\nIf your household income is at or below 150% of the federal poverty level, you may also qualify for grants or vouchers per grandchild each year. These cover clothing, school supplies, respite care, legal services, and medical expenses that aren't covered elsewhere. The grandchild must be 18 or younger, live in your home, and neither parent can live with you.",
