        "intro": "If your parent needs nursing-home-level care but wants to stay home, MI Choice covers comprehensive in-home services that would otherwise cost thousands monthly. The program provides personal care, adult day programs, home-delivered meals, medical equipment, respite care for family caregivers, and care coordination — all the supports needed to live safely at home instead of moving to a facility.\n\nYour parent must be 65+ (or disabled 18+) with monthly income below $2,901 and assets under $9,950. Most importantly, they must qualify for nursing facility level of care through a clinical assessment — meaning they need daily help with activities like bathing, dressing, medication management, or have significant cognitive impairment. Because this replaces expensive nursing home care, participants receive individualized service plans worth potentially $50,000+ annually in care coordination, personal care, and medical supports.",
