        "intro": "If your parent qualifies for nursing home care but wants to stay home, Michigan PACE provides all their medical care, prescriptions, therapy, meals, and daily support through one coordinated team. Instead of juggling separate doctors, insurance claims, and care providers, your parent gets everything from primary care to transportation to adult day services — with no copays if they have Medicaid.\n\nPACE is only available in specific areas of Michigan and requires your parent to be 55+ and certified as needing nursing home level of care (daily help with bathing, dressing, or medication management). Because PACE covers all care under one program, your parent cannot see outside doctors or specialists without PACE approval — the program becomes their complete healthcare system.\n\nIf your parent has both Medicare and Medicaid, PACE costs nothing. If they only have Medicare, they pay a monthly premium based on their income and assets, which PACE will help calculate during enrollment.",
