        "intro": "If your parent is 65+ and struggling with medical costs, Minnesota Medical Assistance can cover doctor visits, hospital care, prescription drugs, and long-term services like home care or assisted living support. Because MA works alongside Medicare for eligible seniors, your parent could get help paying Medicare premiums plus coverage for services Medicare doesn't cover. Income limits vary: up to $1,305/month for disability-based MA or higher limits (up to 138% of federal poverty level) for general coverage. Some seniors qualify automatically based on other benefits they receive, while others must meet income and asset tests.",
