        "intro": "If your parent needs nursing home level care but wants to stay home, Montana's Big Sky Waiver can pay for comprehensive home care services including personal assistance, homemaker services, case management, and medical equipment. The program covers everything from daily personal care to home modifications like ramps and grab bars. Because this waiver allows your parent to receive intensive care at home, they can avoid nursing facility placement while getting the support they need.\n\nYour parent must qualify for Medicaid and demonstrate they need nursing facility level of care (daily help with bathing, dressing, medication management, or mobility). Income must be $967/month or less, and assets must stay under $2,000 for individuals. The program currently has a waiting list, so qualifying doesn't guarantee immediate enrollment.",
