        "intro": "If your parent needs significant daily help with bathing, dressing, or other basic activities, the AD HCBS Waiver can provide home-based services to keep them out of a nursing home. The program covers personal care, home modifications, meal delivery, adult day health, and respite care — all at no cost to families who qualify.\n\nTo qualify, your parent must be 65+ (or any age with a disability), meet Nebraska Medicaid income limits, and pass a clinical assessment showing they need nursing home-level care. Because the assessment is detailed and strict, most applicants need help with at least 3 activities of daily living plus additional health or cognitive issues.\n\nThe Level of Care assessment gets scheduled within 14 days of applying. Home equity cannot exceed $752,000, though your parent can keep their home if they live there or plan to return.",
