        "intro": "If your parent needs nursing home-level care but wants to stay at home, PACE provides everything under one roof: all medical care, medications, transportation to appointments, home care services, and adult day programs. Because PACE coordinates all care through one team, your parent won't juggle multiple doctors, insurance claims, or copays — the program covers it all.\n\nPACE is only available in eastern Nebraska counties (Douglas, Sarpy, and select areas of Cass, Dodge, Saunders, and Washington). Your parent must be 55+ and pass a state assessment proving they need nursing facility-level care (daily help with bathing, dressing, medication management, or mobility). There are no income or asset limits to join, but Medicaid eligibility determines whether it's free or requires monthly premiums.",
