            "question": "My parents are married but only one needs nursing home care. How are assets counted?",
            "answer": "All assets are counted jointly regardless of whose name they're in. However, the community spouse (the one staying at home) can retain up to $157,920 in assets depending on circumstances. This is complex — consider consulting an elder law attorney."
