        "intro": "If your parent is 55+ and needs nursing home-level care but wants to stay home, PACE provides everything through one team: all medical care, prescription drugs, hot meals, transportation, and personal care services. Because PACE covers all services under one program, your parent won't need to coordinate between separate doctors, specialists, or agencies — one interdisciplinary team manages everything.\n\nPACE is only available in specific areas of Oklahoma: Oklahoma City, Shawnee, and parts of Seminole County through Valir PACE, plus LIFE PACE's service area. Your parent must qualify for nursing home-level care (needing daily help with bathing, dressing, or medication management) and meet SoonerCare income and asset limits. If your parent qualifies for Medicaid, PACE has no copays or deductibles. Private pay costs approximately $4,000–$5,000/month.\n\nThe trade-off: your parent must use PACE as their sole healthcare provider. They cannot see outside doctors or specialists except in emergencies, and using unauthorized services means paying out-of-pocket.",
