        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "Can Mom keep seeing her current doctor if she joins PACE?",
            "answer": "No. PACE requires your mom to use their interdisciplinary team as her sole healthcare provider. She cannot see outside doctors, specialists, or other providers except in true emergencies. Using unauthorized services means paying out-of-pocket."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if Mom's income is just over the SoonerCare limit?",
            "answer": "She can still enroll in PACE as a private pay participant for approximately $4,000–$5,000 per month. This covers all the same services but without Medicaid assistance for costs."
          },
          {
            "question": "Does PACE cover nursing home care if Mom needs it later?",
            "answer": "Yes. PACE covers nursing home-level services both at home and in facilities if your mom's needs change. The same PACE team coordinates all care regardless of setting."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can Mom keep her house while in PACE?",
            "answer": "Yes. The primary home is exempt from asset limits for PACE eligibility. She can keep her house regardless of its value."
          },
          {
            "question": "What happens if we move to a different city in Oklahoma?",
            "answer": "PACE is only available in specific service areas. If you move outside your PACE provider's service area, your mom would need to disenroll and find other healthcare coverage."
          },
          {
            "question": "How is PACE different from regular Medicare and Medicaid?",
            "answer": "PACE combines all Medicare and Medicaid benefits under one provider team, plus adds services like transportation, meals, and adult day care. Instead of coordinating between multiple providers, one PACE team manages everything."
          }
        ],
        "phone": null,
        "sourceUrl": "https://oklahoma.gov/ohca/policies-and-rules/xpolicy/medical-assistance-for-adults-and-children-eligibility/programs-of-all-inclusive-care-for-the-elderly-pace-/eligibility-criteria.html",
