        "intro": "If your parent needs daily help with bathing, dressing, or medication management, Utah Medicaid can cover the cost of nursing home care or home-based services. The program has different income limits depending on whether your parent stays at home ($1,255/month) or moves to a nursing home (no strict limit, but most income goes toward care costs). Your parent keeps only $45/month for personal needs in a nursing home, but Medicaid covers all care costs beyond that.\n\nThe program protects some assets — your parent can keep their home (if equity is under $730,000), one car, and personal belongings. If married, the spouse staying at home can keep up to $157,920 in assets and enough income to live independently. Because there are multiple program types with different rules, you'll need a clinical assessment to determine which services your parent qualifies for.",
